WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.048 --> 00:00:09.426
[dark. dramatic music playing]

2
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:51.342
HUMAN VAPOR

3
00:01:01.186 --> 00:01:04.314
[detective] Victim sustained
multiple stab wounds with a bladed weapon

4
00:01:04.397 --> 00:01:07.025
and was deceased
by the time the paramedics arrived.

5
00:01:07.108 --> 00:01:09.235
Did he have anything on him?

6
00:01:09.944 --> 00:01:13.156
[detective] There was a wallet in his bag
and a cellphone.

7
00:01:13.823 --> 00:01:15.241
That was about it.

8
00:01:18.328 --> 00:01:19.954
You looking for something else?

9
00:01:20.622 --> 00:01:22.415
Yeah. You never know.

10
00:01:22.499 --> 00:01:24.000
[officer 1] Everyone's over there.

11
00:01:24.084 --> 00:01:26.377
-[officer 2] That's the scene.
-[officer 1] Yeah.

12
00:01:32.509 --> 00:01:34.928
[phone vibrating]

13
00:01:38.098 --> 00:01:39.182
[Kenji sighs]

14
00:01:41.684 --> 00:01:42.644
Hello.

15
00:01:43.728 --> 00:01:45.730
[Kyoko sighs] How did it go?

16
00:01:48.358 --> 00:01:49.651
Obata…

17
00:01:51.277 --> 00:01:52.362
was murdered.

18
00:01:52.862 --> 00:01:53.863
[Kyoko sighs]

19
00:01:53.947 --> 00:01:55.949
[haunting music playing]

20
00:01:57.408 --> 00:01:58.451
And the journal?

21
00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:04.165
This has nothing to do with you.
Stay out of it.

22
00:02:04.249 --> 00:02:06.251
That's not what I asked.
What about the journal?

23
00:02:06.334 --> 00:02:08.169
I'm telling you to back off.

24
00:02:09.671 --> 00:02:11.673
You almost got yourself killed earlier.

25
00:02:13.216 --> 00:02:15.218
[scoffs] So what?

26
00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:18.054
[Kenji] "So what?"

27
00:02:18.847 --> 00:02:20.723
You could still be a target.

28
00:02:21.516 --> 00:02:24.394
I told them to secure
a safe place for you. Get going.

29
00:02:27.105 --> 00:02:28.231
[sighs]

30
00:02:33.987 --> 00:02:37.323
[Michiko] Excuse me. it looks like
two reporters were witnesses.

31
00:02:38.324 --> 00:02:40.994
-[man] One male. one female. All right.
-[Michiko] Yeah.

32
00:02:42.495 --> 00:02:44.205
[Kyoko] Excuse me. can I talk to you?

33
00:02:45.373 --> 00:02:46.374
[Michiko] Excuse me.

34
00:02:47.458 --> 00:02:49.627
Yeah? What is it?

35
00:02:50.128 --> 00:02:52.046
Why were you tailing the yakuza?

36
00:02:52.714 --> 00:02:54.174
The one who attacked me?

37
00:02:54.966 --> 00:02:58.303
[Michiko sighs]
I'm sorry. I can't disclose that.

38
00:02:59.345 --> 00:03:02.015
You realize I'm asking
as the one who was almost killed?

39
00:03:02.515 --> 00:03:05.018
[Michiko] Maybe you don't know.
so I'll tell you now.

40
00:03:05.101 --> 00:03:06.603
It's against protocol

41
00:03:07.145 --> 00:03:09.856
to share information
regarding ongoing investigations.

42
00:03:10.356 --> 00:03:12.108
Especially with reporters.

43
00:03:13.776 --> 00:03:16.613
And… Okamoto reached out to me.

44
00:03:17.113 --> 00:03:19.616
We're taking you somewhere safe.
You're to stay there.

45
00:03:20.992 --> 00:03:22.493
[Tatsuya] I brought the car.

46
00:03:26.998 --> 00:03:27.916
I'm fine.

47
00:03:29.876 --> 00:03:31.502
I still have work to do.

48
00:03:35.131 --> 00:03:38.718
[Kenji] The victim. Hiroki Obata.
used to be the director of White Center.

49
00:03:38.801 --> 00:03:41.346
After it shut down. he went off the grid.

50
00:03:42.597 --> 00:03:45.016
It appears he was trying
to hand over a White Center journal

51
00:03:45.099 --> 00:03:48.853
from back in the day to Kono.
and it got him killed.

52
00:03:48.937 --> 00:03:51.856
My opinion. it's got
Fujishiro Syndicate written all over it.

53
00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:53.316
They must've wanted the journal.

54
00:03:53.399 --> 00:03:56.194
Jesus Christ. what the hell is going on?

55
00:03:57.111 --> 00:04:00.740
Do you think it means the case
really is connected to the Human Vapor?

56
00:04:00.823 --> 00:04:01.824
[Kenji] Yeah.

57
00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:06.412
The Syndicate's been laying low.
but if they're willing to go this far

58
00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:10.166
then I gotta think that journal's got
some crucial info inside it.

59
00:04:10.708 --> 00:04:12.919
-[man] Mr. Okamoto! Sir!
-[Kenji] Hang on.

60
00:04:13.002 --> 00:04:15.421
Security-cam footage
gave us the suspect's vehicle.

61
00:04:15.505 --> 00:04:17.799
Owner is Shinzo Yamazaki. 32 years old.

62
00:04:17.882 --> 00:04:20.134
He's a member of the Fujishiro Syndicate.

63
00:04:20.218 --> 00:04:22.971
Grab a warrant and track his phone.
He's probably not far.

64
00:04:23.054 --> 00:04:25.515
-I'm on it.
-Sorry. I'm here.

65
00:04:26.182 --> 00:04:27.976
I'll report if there's anything new.

66
00:04:46.494 --> 00:04:47.787
[Yamazaki] Hello?

67
00:04:47.870 --> 00:04:51.124
I took the journal. just like you asked.
I've got it right here.

68
00:04:51.207 --> 00:04:52.792
[lively chatter]

69
00:04:52.875 --> 00:04:55.128
Take pictures of it.
Send them to me immediately.

70
00:04:55.211 --> 00:04:56.713
I need to know what's inside.

71
00:04:57.297 --> 00:04:58.881
[Yamazaki] Huh? Oh. Uh…

72
00:04:58.965 --> 00:05:02.218
I was worried they might track me
so I threw my phone away.

73
00:05:02.302 --> 00:05:06.014
[shouts] You stupid idiot!
What the hell were you thinking?

74
00:05:06.097 --> 00:05:07.348
All right. listen to me.

75
00:05:07.432 --> 00:05:10.727
I don't care how you do it
but I need those pictures sent to me ASAP.

76
00:05:11.227 --> 00:05:12.145
Got that?

77
00:05:12.645 --> 00:05:15.315
If you ever get cornered.
you need to destroy the original.

78
00:05:15.398 --> 00:05:17.400
Am I making myself clear?

79
00:05:17.483 --> 00:05:19.193
[host] Guess what today is?

80
00:05:19.277 --> 00:05:22.155
It's the Turtle Roulette!

81
00:05:22.238 --> 00:05:25.825
-Let's get started!
-[crowd cheering]

82
00:05:25.908 --> 00:05:27.952
-[tense music playing]
-[sighs]

83
00:05:29.287 --> 00:05:31.039
Cell phone. Pictures.

84
00:05:31.122 --> 00:05:33.875
Cell phone. Pictures.
Cell phone. Pictures…

85
00:05:33.958 --> 00:05:37.170
[host] What do you say
we bring in the turtles?

86
00:05:37.253 --> 00:05:40.798
All right! Let's welcome them in
with a big. warm round of applause!

87
00:05:40.882 --> 00:05:42.050
[man 1] Turtles!

88
00:05:42.133 --> 00:05:44.302
[man 2] 20 on Vermilion Bird.
ten on Azure Dragon.

89
00:05:44.385 --> 00:05:46.721
[man 3] Put a good turtle on red for me!

90
00:05:46.804 --> 00:05:48.181
[host] Number one.

91
00:05:48.264 --> 00:05:49.599
Number two.

92
00:05:49.682 --> 00:05:51.517
They're going in!

93
00:05:51.601 --> 00:05:54.145
And there we are. The die has been cast.

94
00:05:54.228 --> 00:05:57.273
Or in this case.
the turtles have been cast. [laughs]

95
00:05:57.357 --> 00:05:59.317
-Here we go!
-[man 4] Spin it!

96
00:05:59.400 --> 00:06:02.779
-[bell ringing]
-[host] Okay! Round and round we go!

97
00:06:02.862 --> 00:06:07.575
All right! What do we think lady luck
will have in store for us tonight?

98
00:06:07.658 --> 00:06:09.702
Folks. place your bets!

99
00:06:09.786 --> 00:06:12.914
Where are the mighty turtles
gonna land this time?

100
00:06:12.997 --> 00:06:16.626
Oh. it's slowing down.
Let's see where we end up. folks!

101
00:06:16.709 --> 00:06:18.628
-And they're off!
-[crowd cheering]

102
00:06:18.711 --> 00:06:21.339
[host] Oh!
A little slow out of the gate here!

103
00:06:23.716 --> 00:06:26.469
-[man 5] Red! Red!
-[host] Number three is starting to move.

104
00:06:26.552 --> 00:06:29.055
Here he comes! He's making his move!

105
00:06:29.138 --> 00:06:30.932
And there we go! Number three is in!

106
00:06:31.015 --> 00:06:32.517
Number three is in Black Tortoise!

107
00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:35.520
Now we anxiously await
the fates of turtles one and two!

108
00:06:35.603 --> 00:06:38.606
Oh. look at that!
Number two is in Azure Dragon!

109
00:06:38.689 --> 00:06:41.192
It looks like number one
has gone into Black Tortoise!

110
00:06:41.275 --> 00:06:44.362
Number one. Black Tortoise.
number two. Azure Dragon.

111
00:06:44.445 --> 00:06:47.782
number three. Black Tortoise.
and that concludes the round!

112
00:06:48.282 --> 00:06:50.827
-[elevator bell dings]
-[music fades out]

113
00:06:50.910 --> 00:06:51.994
[muffled shouting]

114
00:06:52.078 --> 00:06:54.831
-[man 1] It's all crumpled up!
-[man 2] Oh. sorry.

115
00:06:54.914 --> 00:06:56.541
-[man 3] Where is he?
-Inside.

116
00:06:57.041 --> 00:06:59.335
[man 1] It needs to be sealed tight.
you idiot!

117
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:01.129
Do you want the Vapor to get in?

118
00:07:02.296 --> 00:07:03.464
[man 2] Sorry. boss.

119
00:07:04.215 --> 00:07:06.759
[man 1] Hey. moron.
There's a gap right there.

120
00:07:06.843 --> 00:07:08.010
-Are you blind?
-Sorry!

121
00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:09.220
-Fix it!
-Yes. sir!

122
00:07:09.303 --> 00:07:10.555
-Sadaoka.
-Yes. sir?

123
00:07:10.638 --> 00:07:12.765
-You too. It's all messy. dumbass.
-Oh. sorry.

124
00:07:12.849 --> 00:07:15.435
Will you look at this one?
It's like a frame. isn't it?

125
00:07:15.518 --> 00:07:18.604
But for some reason. yours is way off.
What's going on here? Morons!

126
00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:20.022
[gasps fearfully]

127
00:07:20.106 --> 00:07:22.442
-[man 3 laughs]
-Prick.

128
00:07:22.525 --> 00:07:24.944
Man. what's wrong with you?
Don't scare me like that!

129
00:07:25.027 --> 00:07:27.447
-Put that out!
-It's a joke. relax?

130
00:07:27.530 --> 00:07:29.240
Yakuzas are scared of the Human Vapor?

131
00:07:29.323 --> 00:07:32.326
You understand we're not dealing
with a regular human being here?

132
00:07:33.494 --> 00:07:37.665
Yamazaki got a hold of it.
that journal you asked for.

133
00:07:37.748 --> 00:07:38.791
He did?

134
00:07:38.875 --> 00:07:41.377
-Have him bring it down.
-Mm. [clicks tongue]

135
00:07:41.461 --> 00:07:43.254
You know. Dad. I was thinking.

136
00:07:43.754 --> 00:07:47.675
this might be a great opportunity for us
if we take advantage.

137
00:07:49.594 --> 00:07:51.971
Shouldn't we make the first move here?

138
00:07:52.847 --> 00:07:57.393
I say we get in touch with them right away
and get something worthwhile out of it.

139
00:07:58.936 --> 00:08:01.022
-We get in touch?
-Yeah.

140
00:08:02.607 --> 00:08:04.150
Think about it. Up until now.

141
00:08:04.233 --> 00:08:07.153
we've been doing all the dirty work
for those guys.

142
00:08:09.280 --> 00:08:13.284
I think we blackmail them
using this journal that Yamazaki stole.

143
00:08:16.537 --> 00:08:17.455
[boss sighs]

144
00:08:17.538 --> 00:08:19.415
-Hey!
-[men] Yes. sir?

145
00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:22.084
The boss is about to make a call.
Get lost.

146
00:08:22.168 --> 00:08:23.002
[men] Yes. sir.

147
00:08:24.295 --> 00:08:25.421
Excuse us.

148
00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:31.010
Hello!

149
00:08:31.093 --> 00:08:34.555
Well. well. it's been a while.
hasn't it? [laughs]

150
00:08:34.639 --> 00:08:38.226
Yeah. and it looks like
we got our hands on the journal first.

151
00:08:39.352 --> 00:08:41.312
I'm guessing you guys want it too?

152
00:08:41.979 --> 00:08:42.813
Ah?

153
00:08:42.897 --> 00:08:44.774
How much is the journal worth to you?

154
00:08:45.733 --> 00:08:48.653
Whoa. whoa. what the hell
are you talking about. asshole?

155
00:08:48.736 --> 00:08:50.696
So what? I'm the next target. then?

156
00:08:50.780 --> 00:08:52.365
Ah? You son of a bitch.

157
00:08:52.448 --> 00:08:55.117
You know I could expose this
to the public if I wanted to?

158
00:08:55.201 --> 00:08:57.119
Then which one of us would be screwed?

159
00:08:57.203 --> 00:08:58.037
Huh?

160
00:09:00.164 --> 00:09:01.624
[laughs]

161
00:09:01.707 --> 00:09:04.794
Then I'd hurry up
and get your checkbook out!

162
00:09:05.670 --> 00:09:06.629
How'd it go?

163
00:09:06.712 --> 00:09:07.880
Ah…

164
00:09:08.381 --> 00:09:10.841
They're panicking. I can tell.

165
00:09:11.467 --> 00:09:12.760
They'll pay 300 million.

166
00:09:12.843 --> 00:09:15.137
I'd say that sounds pretty damn good.

167
00:09:15.721 --> 00:09:17.139
Can we count on that?

168
00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:19.850
-Maybe. We'll see.
-Right.

169
00:09:20.351 --> 00:09:22.728
For now. grab a bunch of guys.

170
00:09:22.812 --> 00:09:25.106
-Meet at headquarters.
-[son] Got it.

171
00:09:30.403 --> 00:09:31.529
Hey. Dad?

172
00:09:34.031 --> 00:09:37.201
If it works out and we end up
catching this vapor guy…

173
00:09:39.412 --> 00:09:40.997
can we do a Parfinee?

174
00:09:41.998 --> 00:09:43.624
I still have my old knives.

175
00:09:43.708 --> 00:09:44.667
[boss] Huh?

176
00:09:45.167 --> 00:09:47.295
We haven't done that in over three years.

177
00:09:51.132 --> 00:09:53.175
[son breathes heavily]

178
00:09:55.845 --> 00:09:57.096
[boss laughs]

179
00:09:57.179 --> 00:09:59.265
[both laughing]

180
00:09:59.765 --> 00:10:01.767
[piercing string note plays. fades]

181
00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:10.484
[detective] Suspect's vehicle located.
License plate ends in 2-6-8.

182
00:10:10.985 --> 00:10:12.820
Nishiizu. Nihara.

183
00:10:13.738 --> 00:10:15.531
That's right. Around the boat dock.

184
00:10:16.073 --> 00:10:18.576
Suspect appears to be on the run.

185
00:10:18.659 --> 00:10:20.036
Possibly injured.

186
00:10:20.995 --> 00:10:22.663
[woman 1] I'm taking the picture.

187
00:10:22.747 --> 00:10:24.290
-Five. four…
-Hurry! Come on. hurry!

188
00:10:24.373 --> 00:10:27.001
[both] Three. two. one…

189
00:10:27.084 --> 00:10:28.127
[both] Huh?

190
00:10:28.210 --> 00:10:29.587
-Hey! Hey!
-Hey!

191
00:10:29.670 --> 00:10:32.173
-Hey! What the hell?
-Momo! Wait!

192
00:10:32.256 --> 00:10:34.091
-[Momo] Stop!
-Momo! Ah!

193
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:36.927
-[Momo] Hey! You! Stop right there!
-[woman 2] Momo!

194
00:10:37.762 --> 00:10:38.888
[Momo screams]

195
00:10:39.513 --> 00:10:41.724
[woman 2] Momo! Somebody help!

196
00:10:41.807 --> 00:10:43.184
-Let's go! Come on!
-Help!

197
00:10:43.267 --> 00:10:45.478
[woman 2 squeals] Momo!

198
00:10:45.561 --> 00:10:46.771
Help!

199
00:10:48.939 --> 00:10:50.107
Momo!

200
00:10:51.067 --> 00:10:52.568
[woman 2 squeals]

201
00:10:52.652 --> 00:10:53.736
Momo!

202
00:10:55.988 --> 00:10:58.366
[Tatsuya] All this bullshit
over one stupid journal?

203
00:10:58.449 --> 00:11:00.326
What's so important about it?

204
00:11:01.744 --> 00:11:04.914
Well. based on everything Obata said…

205
00:11:06.165 --> 00:11:09.543
apparently all the names
of the people the Human Vapor is targeting

206
00:11:09.627 --> 00:11:11.003
are written in there.

207
00:11:12.254 --> 00:11:13.255
[Tatsuya] Huh?

208
00:11:14.423 --> 00:11:16.842
Hold on.
doesn't that mean we're in danger too?

209
00:11:16.926 --> 00:11:18.928
So if we report this story.

210
00:11:19.011 --> 00:11:21.305
we could quietly get taken out.
couldn't we?

211
00:11:21.389 --> 00:11:24.183
If you don't like it.
being a reporter's not for you.

212
00:11:24.266 --> 00:11:27.228
-If it kills me. I wanna be a reporter.
-Wait. hold on.

213
00:11:30.147 --> 00:11:31.524
How did the yakuza

214
00:11:32.024 --> 00:11:34.902
know that I was meeting with Obata at all?

215
00:11:37.822 --> 00:11:39.073
[Tatsuya] Good point.

216
00:11:40.908 --> 00:11:42.827
Do you think you could've been bugged?

217
00:11:42.910 --> 00:11:45.413
[tense music playing]

218
00:11:45.496 --> 00:11:47.998
[inhales] I doubt that.

219
00:11:48.082 --> 00:11:49.166
[groans]

220
00:11:49.917 --> 00:11:52.044
Here. gimme your phone for one second.

221
00:11:53.045 --> 00:11:55.047
[dramatic music playing]

222
00:12:11.522 --> 00:12:13.566
-Here you go.
-Thanks.

223
00:12:13.649 --> 00:12:14.775
-So?
-[Tatsuya exhales]

224
00:12:15.276 --> 00:12:16.986
Just gimme another second here.

225
00:12:19.864 --> 00:12:21.031
Hmm…

226
00:12:21.741 --> 00:12:23.159
Yeah. there ya go. I knew it.

227
00:12:23.242 --> 00:12:24.785
-You were bugged.
-What?

228
00:12:26.036 --> 00:12:29.665
Pretty nasty malware virus was installed
on your phone at some point.

229
00:12:30.374 --> 00:12:35.004
It's programmed to record and save
your phone calls' audio as AMR files.

230
00:12:35.504 --> 00:12:38.382
Then it automatically sends them
to a specific server.

231
00:12:39.008 --> 00:12:41.677
Where did you learn how do all this stuff?

232
00:12:42.303 --> 00:12:43.387
[Tatsuya chuckles]

233
00:12:43.888 --> 00:12:48.142
Well. uh. I actually entered
a lot of hacking contests in university.

234
00:12:51.395 --> 00:12:53.814
Wouldn't that have been
a better line of work for you?

235
00:12:54.857 --> 00:12:55.691
No.

236
00:12:56.484 --> 00:12:58.444
I wanna be a reporter.
even if it kills me.

237
00:12:58.527 --> 00:12:59.904
Okay. but it's still weird.

238
00:13:00.404 --> 00:13:02.782
I don't remember clicking
on anything suspicious.

239
00:13:02.865 --> 00:13:04.533
Emails or links or anything.

240
00:13:04.617 --> 00:13:05.618
[Tatsuya] Mm.

241
00:13:08.621 --> 00:13:09.830
No. That's not it.

242
00:13:09.914 --> 00:13:12.082
Someone installed this directly
on your phone.

243
00:13:12.166 --> 00:13:13.042
[Kyoko] But how?

244
00:13:14.168 --> 00:13:16.504
I never let anyone touch my phone.

245
00:13:18.547 --> 00:13:21.217
[male detective] Abe. that's too much.

246
00:13:21.884 --> 00:13:23.511
We checked your phone

247
00:13:23.594 --> 00:13:26.347
and didn't flag anything
that was of concern.

248
00:13:26.430 --> 00:13:27.807
Sorry about that.

249
00:13:28.724 --> 00:13:30.935
Uh. you're free to go now. Thank you.

250
00:13:31.018 --> 00:13:33.062
[suspenseful music playing]

251
00:13:33.145 --> 00:13:34.146
[Tatsuya] Hey.

252
00:13:35.314 --> 00:13:37.274
I deleted the virus off your phone.

253
00:13:38.734 --> 00:13:39.568
Yes.

254
00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:41.654
[dramatic music playing]

255
00:13:55.292 --> 00:13:57.920
[panting]

256
00:13:58.003 --> 00:14:00.130
-Let's split up and cover more ground.
-Agreed.

257
00:14:00.631 --> 00:14:02.049
I'll check over this way.

258
00:14:02.842 --> 00:14:05.386
I'll go up there. okay? We'll circle back.

259
00:14:12.726 --> 00:14:13.561
MISSING

260
00:14:13.644 --> 00:14:15.312
LOCATION UNKNOWN

261
00:14:15.396 --> 00:14:17.731
MISSING: TAKUYA NODA

262
00:14:23.320 --> 00:14:25.447
[tense. sinister music playing]

263
00:14:31.537 --> 00:14:33.622
[breathing heavily]

264
00:14:33.706 --> 00:14:35.791
[suppressing laughter]

265
00:14:44.842 --> 00:14:46.802
DIED OF ILLNESS

266
00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:47.761
WHEREABOUTS UNKNOWN

267
00:14:51.891 --> 00:14:52.850
[sighs]

268
00:14:52.933 --> 00:14:55.019
[tense. sinister music continues]

269
00:15:19.001 --> 00:15:20.836
MISSING
REN TSUTSUMIDA

270
00:15:25.257 --> 00:15:26.425
[Yamazaki] Mufu?

271
00:15:28.344 --> 00:15:29.637
-[twig snaps]
-[gasps]

272
00:15:32.431 --> 00:15:33.807
[detective] Yamazaki.

273
00:15:36.769 --> 00:15:38.938
What's wrong? What?

274
00:15:39.021 --> 00:15:41.065
Don't you think you're overreacting?

275
00:15:41.607 --> 00:15:43.108
Why don't you lower that?

276
00:15:44.318 --> 00:15:46.195
What the hell is going on here?

277
00:15:46.278 --> 00:15:48.280
Why are the police after me?

278
00:15:48.781 --> 00:15:50.324
What about you? Huh?

279
00:15:50.866 --> 00:15:53.118
You were told explicitly
to destroy that journal.

280
00:15:53.202 --> 00:15:54.453
but you ran away with it.

281
00:15:54.536 --> 00:15:57.790
That's not what we agreed on. is it?

282
00:16:05.464 --> 00:16:07.716
-[breathes heavily]
-You read the journal.

283
00:16:08.509 --> 00:16:09.426
Didn't you?

284
00:16:09.510 --> 00:16:10.511
No.

285
00:16:10.594 --> 00:16:11.679
No! I didn't!

286
00:16:20.229 --> 00:16:21.188
[tuts]

287
00:16:21.271 --> 00:16:22.940
[sighs]

288
00:16:23.482 --> 00:16:25.359
Oh. goddammit.

289
00:16:25.442 --> 00:16:27.236
WHITE CENTER WORK JOURNAL
MESSAGE OPENED

290
00:16:27.319 --> 00:16:29.321
[footsteps approaching]

291
00:16:37.871 --> 00:16:38.872
[Kenji] Yoshida.

292
00:16:40.958 --> 00:16:43.293
-What'd you do?
-[Yoshida] Look…

293
00:16:43.377 --> 00:16:44.545
[Kenji] You shot him?

294
00:16:45.087 --> 00:16:48.090
I had no choice.
He… he had a knife on him.

295
00:16:48.173 --> 00:16:50.634
The idiot started coming at me.
I told him to stop.

296
00:16:51.135 --> 00:16:52.386
I had to.

297
00:16:53.679 --> 00:16:57.099
-[detective] Jesus…
-[Yoshida] Don't bother. He's dead.

298
00:16:58.434 --> 00:16:59.977
Sorry. I'm just a little shaken.

299
00:17:00.060 --> 00:17:02.730
If I hadn't shot him.
he would've killed me. Hey. Motoyama?

300
00:17:02.813 --> 00:17:04.982
-[Motoyama] Yes?
-[Yoshida] Call this in.

301
00:17:05.983 --> 00:17:08.861
-It was an accident. You got that?
-[phone vibrating]

302
00:17:08.944 --> 00:17:10.738
[Yoshida sighs] Jesus. that was close.

303
00:17:10.821 --> 00:17:12.698
KYOKO KONO

304
00:17:12.781 --> 00:17:13.824
Yeah?

305
00:17:14.658 --> 00:17:17.286
Kyoko. are you at the secure location?

306
00:17:17.369 --> 00:17:18.454
Kenji. listen to me.

307
00:17:19.038 --> 00:17:22.875
When I last came in for questioning.
there was a detective with glasses

308
00:17:22.958 --> 00:17:25.753
who took my phone. right? Who is he?

309
00:17:26.962 --> 00:17:29.673
[Yoshida] I had no choice but to shoot.
I gave him warnings.

310
00:17:29.757 --> 00:17:30.924
[Kenji] Why are you asking?

311
00:17:31.008 --> 00:17:35.304
I find it a bit weird. don't you?
The yakuza knowing I was talking to Obata?

312
00:17:36.346 --> 00:17:37.222
Plus.

313
00:17:38.140 --> 00:17:40.726
I just checked my phone. and. Kenji.

314
00:17:40.809 --> 00:17:43.020
there was some kind of malware installed
on it.

315
00:17:43.103 --> 00:17:44.229
It was bugged.

316
00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:45.731
You sure?

317
00:17:46.231 --> 00:17:48.067
And apparently the virus

318
00:17:48.567 --> 00:17:51.320
would've had to be installed directly
into my phone.

319
00:17:54.490 --> 00:17:56.575
[exhales] You think…

320
00:17:56.658 --> 00:17:59.953
[Kyoko] It's the only time I've been
separated from my phone recently.

321
00:18:00.829 --> 00:18:03.957
So… it must be that detective.

322
00:18:05.167 --> 00:18:07.419
Or else someone else
inside the police force

323
00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:10.422
is colluding with the yakuza.

324
00:18:10.506 --> 00:18:13.383
[Motoyama] Male fugitive has been located.
He's injured…

325
00:18:13.467 --> 00:18:15.636
I'm sorry. but that's not possible.

326
00:18:18.013 --> 00:18:19.348
[sighs]

327
00:18:19.431 --> 00:18:21.433
You still haven't answered my question.

328
00:18:21.975 --> 00:18:23.102
[Kenji] What question?

329
00:18:24.019 --> 00:18:25.104
The journal.

330
00:18:27.231 --> 00:18:28.273
The journal

331
00:18:29.441 --> 00:18:30.818
has been destroyed.

332
00:18:31.819 --> 00:18:33.529
So you can back away from this now.

333
00:18:33.612 --> 00:18:35.906
It's too dangerous for you
to get more involved.

334
00:18:37.866 --> 00:18:38.909
Understood?

335
00:18:44.164 --> 00:18:45.249
[sighs]

336
00:18:51.964 --> 00:18:54.383
-[people shouting. chanting]
-[whistles blowing]

337
00:18:56.844 --> 00:18:58.512
-Hey. everyone.
-[man 1] How are you?

338
00:18:58.595 --> 00:19:00.055
-[woman] Hey.
-[Tatsuya] Hey.

339
00:19:00.139 --> 00:19:02.015
Kyoko. Here.

340
00:19:03.267 --> 00:19:05.853
This just came in
from the Metro PD reporter.

341
00:19:06.603 --> 00:19:09.648
Apparently. Shinzo Yamazaki.
the man shot by police.

342
00:19:09.731 --> 00:19:11.733
was with the Fujishiro Syndicate.

343
00:19:12.901 --> 00:19:14.862
SHINZO YAMAZAKI
SECURITY CAMERA FOOTAGE

344
00:19:14.945 --> 00:19:19.324
[Kyoko] Which would mean that the police
showed up at the meeting place with Obata

345
00:19:19.408 --> 00:19:22.202
because they were following the Syndicate?

346
00:19:22.286 --> 00:19:24.705
-[Yoko] Hmm.
-Wait. hold on.

347
00:19:26.206 --> 00:19:30.169
It doesn't make… Why would Yamazaki go
through the trouble of stealing a phone?

348
00:19:30.252 --> 00:19:31.253
ROBBED PHONE OFF WOMAN

349
00:19:31.336 --> 00:19:34.756
[Yoko] Maybe he knew he was cornered
and needed to contact someone?

350
00:19:35.841 --> 00:19:38.302
He could've been
sending something to someone

351
00:19:38.385 --> 00:19:40.429
right before he burned the journal.

352
00:19:43.182 --> 00:19:45.893
He could've taken pictures
and then sent them to somebody!

353
00:19:46.560 --> 00:19:49.229
Who would he send that to?
The Human Vapor and the yakuza?

354
00:19:49.730 --> 00:19:51.064
You think they're connected?

355
00:19:52.608 --> 00:19:55.444
Yoko. do you know
where I can find the Syndicate?

356
00:19:55.527 --> 00:19:57.446
Mm. One second.

357
00:19:57.988 --> 00:20:01.700
[Tatsuya] The Human Vapor… The yakuza…

358
00:20:02.242 --> 00:20:04.286
What the hell is the connection?

359
00:20:04.369 --> 00:20:06.371
[indistinct shouting outside]

360
00:20:08.457 --> 00:20:12.127
[man shouts outside]
JNT. stop pushing the Human Vapor!

361
00:20:12.211 --> 00:20:13.879
-[whistles blowing]
-[crowd shouting]

362
00:20:16.256 --> 00:20:19.301
[man shouts]
Kirishima for Governor of Tokyo!

363
00:20:21.386 --> 00:20:24.806
Yeah. They're from the group
supporting Kazumi Kirishima.

364
00:20:25.557 --> 00:20:27.100
She's coming up here right now.

365
00:20:27.851 --> 00:20:29.478
-Are you sure?
-[reporter] Yeah.

366
00:20:29.561 --> 00:20:31.146
[director] I'll handle it. ma'am--

367
00:20:31.230 --> 00:20:33.440
[woman] Can I have your attention
for a moment?

368
00:20:34.608 --> 00:20:38.487
Everyone at this station insists
on reporting about the Human Vapor.

369
00:20:38.570 --> 00:20:40.113
all day. every day.

370
00:20:40.197 --> 00:20:43.033
It's fearmongering!
You are terrifying all the voters.

371
00:20:43.116 --> 00:20:47.162
So more and more of them are calling
for Governor Miura to be reelected.

372
00:20:47.246 --> 00:20:49.206
[director] May we discuss this privately--

373
00:20:49.289 --> 00:20:51.541
[Kirishima] This station is biased
to my opponent!

374
00:20:51.625 --> 00:20:54.378
[man] She's not wrong.
The coverage has been ridiculous!

375
00:20:54.461 --> 00:20:56.338
[Kirishima]
It's for the good of the people!

376
00:20:56.421 --> 00:20:59.800
-Can we get security in here?
-Your station is creating panic.

377
00:21:00.550 --> 00:21:03.095
[reporter] The election
is right around the corner.

378
00:21:03.804 --> 00:21:05.847
It's not worth getting
in the middle of it.

379
00:21:05.931 --> 00:21:08.600
-It'll be done soon.
-[Kirishima] This station is biased!

380
00:21:08.684 --> 00:21:12.187
-[director] There's a conference room--
-[man] She's trying to serve the people.

381
00:21:15.148 --> 00:21:18.986
[man] I already told you guys.
I was wandering around and got lost.

382
00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:22.489
Then I met up with my buddies
in the parking lot

383
00:21:22.572 --> 00:21:24.241
and got caught up in this shit.

384
00:21:24.324 --> 00:21:26.034
[handcuffs clicking]

385
00:21:26.118 --> 00:21:30.163
Seriously. though. are we almost done?
This is taking forever.

386
00:21:33.667 --> 00:21:35.877
[Kenji] I want you to take a look at this.

387
00:21:35.961 --> 00:21:37.963
[chilling music playing]

388
00:21:38.547 --> 00:21:39.965
That's you. isn't it?

389
00:21:45.053 --> 00:21:46.138
And this.

390
00:21:47.055 --> 00:21:48.098
And this.

391
00:21:49.766 --> 00:21:50.934
And this.

392
00:21:54.938 --> 00:21:57.357
What's your relationship
with the Syndicate?

393
00:21:58.191 --> 00:22:01.153
Fujishiro Syndicate is no joke. kid.
I'd tell us now.

394
00:22:01.653 --> 00:22:03.655
[tense music playing]

395
00:22:05.782 --> 00:22:07.159
[sighs]

396
00:22:10.037 --> 00:22:12.414
I wouldn't say it's a relationship.

397
00:22:14.916 --> 00:22:17.544
They just paid me
to do some of their dirty work for them.

398
00:22:17.627 --> 00:22:19.046
That's all it is. okay?

399
00:22:20.005 --> 00:22:21.506
So what did you do?

400
00:22:29.514 --> 00:22:30.807
Well… [sighs]

401
00:22:32.809 --> 00:22:34.686
They told me to steal a journal.

402
00:22:36.355 --> 00:22:39.024
But that woman
didn't have that stupid journal.

403
00:22:39.858 --> 00:22:42.277
So I was like. "Oh snap."

404
00:22:47.407 --> 00:22:50.202
[Kyoko] If the Fujishiro Syndicate
is running a gambling den.

405
00:22:50.285 --> 00:22:52.704
maybe we could get someone
in there. undercover.

406
00:22:53.205 --> 00:22:55.665
That's gonna be tough.
It's strictly members only.

407
00:22:56.166 --> 00:22:59.419
-Can't just walk in.
-Oh. uh. does anyone know a member?

408
00:22:59.503 --> 00:23:02.547
-We need eyes in there now.
-Uh. we could plant a camera in there.

409
00:23:02.631 --> 00:23:04.549
Yeah… I don't know about that.

410
00:23:04.633 --> 00:23:06.885
[Kyoko] Hmm. might be too risky.

411
00:23:07.386 --> 00:23:10.389
Can we zoom in
from one of the surrounding buildings?

412
00:23:12.057 --> 00:23:13.850
-[Tatsuya] That could work!
-Huh?

413
00:23:14.643 --> 00:23:18.271
If we use a directional microphone.
we'd probably be able to hear them.

414
00:23:18.355 --> 00:23:20.732
-Even with background noise.
-That's a great idea!

415
00:23:20.816 --> 00:23:22.025
Then you're in luck.

416
00:23:22.526 --> 00:23:25.737
There's an abandoned house we use
when we're surveilling the Syndicate.

417
00:23:25.821 --> 00:23:27.030
Shall we give that a shot?

418
00:23:27.114 --> 00:23:28.657
[Kyoko] Let's go with that plan.

419
00:23:28.740 --> 00:23:30.492
-[Tatsuya] All right!
-[man] Great.

420
00:23:30.575 --> 00:23:32.577
[suspenseful music playing]

421
00:23:37.791 --> 00:23:39.543
-[man 1] Gimme that.
-[man 2] Here.

422
00:23:43.088 --> 00:23:45.590
[Tatsuya] This is it. You guys ready?

423
00:23:46.716 --> 00:23:47.801
[man] Here we go.

424
00:23:53.640 --> 00:23:55.892
[Tatsuya] Come on. Hurry.

425
00:24:00.730 --> 00:24:02.399
-[Tatsuya] Go on.
-[man] Oh. thanks.

426
00:24:05.277 --> 00:24:06.403
[Tatsuya] Let's do it.

427
00:24:06.903 --> 00:24:08.947
[Kyoko] The camera needs to be…

428
00:24:09.030 --> 00:24:10.073
[sighs]

429
00:24:11.741 --> 00:24:13.368
Yeah. Here.

430
00:24:13.910 --> 00:24:14.911
[man] Perfect.

431
00:24:16.121 --> 00:24:17.539
-[man] Tripod.
-[Tatsuya] Got it.

432
00:24:23.170 --> 00:24:24.296
[woman] Careful.

433
00:24:25.213 --> 00:24:26.298
[Tatsuya] Stay low.

434
00:24:26.923 --> 00:24:28.592
[Kyoko] Okay. it's in place.

435
00:24:31.845 --> 00:24:33.263
We're good to go.

436
00:24:43.565 --> 00:24:44.983
[static over earphones]

437
00:24:45.066 --> 00:24:46.067
[boss] Hey.

438
00:24:47.652 --> 00:24:48.487
Hey!

439
00:24:49.779 --> 00:24:52.157
Why are you wasting your time. asshole?

440
00:24:53.742 --> 00:24:55.785
You shot Yamazaki!

441
00:24:56.286 --> 00:24:58.163
That's why we can't trust you guys.

442
00:24:59.456 --> 00:25:00.582
Oh. right.

443
00:25:01.291 --> 00:25:03.043
Did you get the picture I sent you?

444
00:25:05.045 --> 00:25:08.215
Now we're the only ones
who know what was in the journal.

445
00:25:08.298 --> 00:25:09.925
You know what that means. right?

446
00:25:11.301 --> 00:25:14.596
Come back empty handed.
and we won't have further need of you.

447
00:25:15.555 --> 00:25:18.683
Is that understood. you useless idiot?

448
00:25:19.518 --> 00:25:22.604
Now. hurry up and do your damn job!

449
00:25:22.687 --> 00:25:26.233
I want the Human Vapor caught immediately!

450
00:25:30.237 --> 00:25:31.905
[Kenji] Three entrances in total.

451
00:25:31.988 --> 00:25:34.032
-Squad leaders need to be cautious.
-Got it.

452
00:25:34.115 --> 00:25:37.369
Sir! We got the warrant
for the Fujishiro Syndicate.

453
00:25:37.452 --> 00:25:39.412
-You heard her. let's move.
-Copy that.

454
00:25:39.496 --> 00:25:43.667
[officer] We have units making their way
to the scene now. Please stand by.

455
00:25:44.167 --> 00:25:46.962
I'm not much of a spicy-food gal anyway.

456
00:25:47.045 --> 00:25:50.799
But you know the company is
the more important thing.

457
00:25:50.882 --> 00:25:53.593
-Might be fun. huh?
-I don't know. Maybe…

458
00:25:58.265 --> 00:25:59.558
[panting]

459
00:25:59.641 --> 00:26:00.725
Look. sir!

460
00:26:00.809 --> 00:26:02.811
[tense music playing]

461
00:26:04.104 --> 00:26:05.230
[boss] He's here.

462
00:26:05.730 --> 00:26:06.856
[all gasp]

463
00:26:07.774 --> 00:26:10.360
All right. let's get the swords out.

464
00:26:12.112 --> 00:26:14.114
[tense music continues]

465
00:26:27.210 --> 00:26:31.214
[host] Okay. this next one is from 2003.

466
00:26:31.298 --> 00:26:34.509
No history of asthma.
influenza. or mycoplasma.

467
00:26:34.593 --> 00:26:36.261
No history of smoking.

468
00:26:36.344 --> 00:26:38.805
Zero damage to the units themselves.

469
00:26:39.306 --> 00:26:42.809
These are the lungs of a perfectly healthy
23-year-old man.

470
00:26:43.310 --> 00:26:45.604
How about we start the bidding
at 15 million?

471
00:26:45.687 --> 00:26:47.355
15 million yen over here!

472
00:26:47.439 --> 00:26:49.899
-17 million yen!
-[man 1] 20 million. Yes.

473
00:26:50.942 --> 00:26:52.944
[host] Yes. sir. 20 million.

474
00:26:55.488 --> 00:26:57.240
Yes. Now we have 25 million.

475
00:26:57.741 --> 00:26:59.159
[tense music playing]

476
00:26:59.242 --> 00:27:00.744
-[host] 30 million!
-[murmuring]

477
00:27:00.827 --> 00:27:01.745
[man 2] 30.

478
00:27:02.871 --> 00:27:05.540
-[host] Anyone else? Do I have 35?
-[man 3 coughs]

479
00:27:05.624 --> 00:27:06.916
[host] 35? No?

480
00:27:07.000 --> 00:27:10.837
Then. sold for 30 million yen
to the gentleman right over here.

481
00:27:10.920 --> 00:27:12.922
-[young man crying]
-[bell rings]

482
00:27:14.716 --> 00:27:15.842
[crying continues]

483
00:27:15.925 --> 00:27:18.887
[host] Next up. this is from 2003…

484
00:27:18.970 --> 00:27:20.180
[man 4] Oh! Oh my God!

485
00:27:20.263 --> 00:27:21.473
[soft whooshing]

486
00:27:21.556 --> 00:27:23.266
[people screaming]

487
00:27:23.350 --> 00:27:25.560
[woman screams]

488
00:27:29.731 --> 00:27:31.566
[whooshing intensifies]

489
00:27:35.528 --> 00:27:37.697
[tense. dramatic music playing]

490
00:27:43.703 --> 00:27:44.913
[music stops abruptly]

491
00:27:52.087 --> 00:27:53.046
[yelling]

492
00:27:53.129 --> 00:27:55.215
[tense. dramatic music resumes]

493
00:28:04.432 --> 00:28:06.101
-Get the car.
-Yes. sir.

494
00:28:07.060 --> 00:28:08.311
Let's go.

495
00:28:08.395 --> 00:28:09.604
[glass shatters]

496
00:28:09.688 --> 00:28:11.606
[indistinct shouting]

497
00:28:15.819 --> 00:28:17.696
[screaming]

498
00:28:18.279 --> 00:28:19.781
Uh. I'll be right back.

499
00:28:20.490 --> 00:28:21.616
Huh? Hey!

500
00:28:21.700 --> 00:28:22.701
Where are you going?

501
00:28:23.827 --> 00:28:27.122
Oh! Number one's in Black Tortoise!

502
00:28:27.205 --> 00:28:28.498
Come on. boss!

503
00:28:28.581 --> 00:28:31.251
[host] Oh. and now number two
is on the move as well!

504
00:28:31.334 --> 00:28:33.712
-There he goes!
-[man] Move! Get out of the way!

505
00:28:33.795 --> 00:28:36.840
-Move now! Get the hell out of the way!
-Move!

506
00:28:36.923 --> 00:28:38.925
-[woman screams]
-[man] Move. goddammit!

507
00:28:39.008 --> 00:28:40.510
Come on. boss!

508
00:28:45.724 --> 00:28:48.184
Boss! Hey. you okay? Boss? Boss!

509
00:28:48.268 --> 00:28:50.145
-Move!
-Hurry up!

510
00:28:50.937 --> 00:28:52.063
[boss gasps]

511
00:28:52.147 --> 00:28:53.690
[wheezes]

512
00:28:53.773 --> 00:28:54.816
[son yells]

513
00:28:55.859 --> 00:28:56.860
[whimpers]

514
00:28:57.652 --> 00:28:58.778
[yells]

515
00:29:00.947 --> 00:29:02.240
[groaning]

516
00:29:13.168 --> 00:29:15.420
-[sirens wailing]
-[dramatic music continues]

517
00:29:22.010 --> 00:29:23.261
[Kenji] Huh?

518
00:29:25.555 --> 00:29:26.431
What?

519
00:29:27.390 --> 00:29:28.391
[exhales] Turn around!

520
00:29:28.475 --> 00:29:29.809
[tires screech]

521
00:29:33.855 --> 00:29:34.856
[car horn beeps]

522
00:29:36.524 --> 00:29:40.570
Excuse me. we're on official business.
You need to move immediately. thank you.

523
00:29:41.196 --> 00:29:42.697
Please clear the road!

524
00:29:42.781 --> 00:29:44.866
-[boss] Go faster!
-[man] Look out!

525
00:29:44.949 --> 00:29:46.618
[boss] Step on it! Come on!

526
00:29:54.667 --> 00:29:56.336
He's catching up!

527
00:29:58.421 --> 00:29:59.589
[boss grunts]

528
00:29:59.672 --> 00:30:00.673
[man] Go. go. go!

529
00:30:07.430 --> 00:30:09.182
[horn blares]

530
00:30:09.265 --> 00:30:10.683
[tires screech]

531
00:30:20.360 --> 00:30:21.653
[horn beeps]

532
00:30:21.736 --> 00:30:23.738
[dramatic music continues]

533
00:30:25.949 --> 00:30:27.700
-[yelling]
-[man] Watch out!

534
00:30:27.784 --> 00:30:28.910
-Shit!
-[boss] He's here!

535
00:30:28.993 --> 00:30:30.411
Oh God. oh God. oh God!

536
00:30:30.495 --> 00:30:32.372
[car horn beeping]

537
00:30:38.044 --> 00:30:40.505
[glass crackling]

538
00:30:40.588 --> 00:30:41.923
-[boss yelps]
-[man grunts]

539
00:30:42.006 --> 00:30:43.967
[repeated banging on car]

540
00:30:44.050 --> 00:30:45.301
[man] What's he doing? Huh?

541
00:30:45.385 --> 00:30:46.845
Up! Look! Up. up. up!

542
00:30:46.928 --> 00:30:49.764
-[boss] What the…
-[man] He's on top of us! On the roof!

543
00:30:49.848 --> 00:30:53.059
-[driver] Where?
-[man] The roof of the car. you moron!

544
00:30:53.142 --> 00:30:54.352
[driver] The roof?

545
00:30:55.979 --> 00:30:56.855
[men yelp]

546
00:30:58.022 --> 00:30:59.732
[gas hissing]

547
00:31:03.528 --> 00:31:05.989
[men yelling fearfully]

548
00:31:06.072 --> 00:31:09.409
Bulletproof glass. asshole!
It's not gonna break!

549
00:31:09.492 --> 00:31:10.994
-It is. right?
-[driver] What?

550
00:31:11.077 --> 00:31:12.954
-It's bulletproof glass?
-[driver] What?

551
00:31:13.037 --> 00:31:15.456
[boss] Tell me it's bulletproof glass!

552
00:31:16.082 --> 00:31:20.003
Check the inspection certificate!
The vehicle inspection certificate!

553
00:31:20.503 --> 00:31:22.672
-It is bulletproof.
-[boss] Oh. thank God!

554
00:31:22.755 --> 00:31:25.216
-[driver] Bro. bro. bro!
-[man] Whoa! What's he doing now?

555
00:31:25.717 --> 00:31:27.510
Don't worry. he can't break in!

556
00:31:27.594 --> 00:31:29.762
[driver] Whoa!
Here he comes! Here he comes!

557
00:31:29.846 --> 00:31:32.140
-Just keep going. keep driving!
-[driver] Yes. sir.

558
00:31:32.223 --> 00:31:34.475
[boss] Get outta here. you son of a bitch!

559
00:31:37.145 --> 00:31:39.314
That was a close one. you idiot!

560
00:31:39.397 --> 00:31:41.357
[dramatic music playing]

561
00:31:41.441 --> 00:31:43.067
He's still on our ass!

562
00:31:43.151 --> 00:31:44.485
-Look!
-Huh?

563
00:31:44.569 --> 00:31:46.362
-He's right there!
-[man] Up front!

564
00:31:46.446 --> 00:31:48.823
-Look out!
-[horn blares]

565
00:31:48.907 --> 00:31:50.867
[driver gasps. then cheers]

566
00:31:50.950 --> 00:31:52.327
[boss] Faster. come on!

567
00:31:52.410 --> 00:31:55.163
-[man] We gotta lose him!
-[boss] Back off. son of a bitch!

568
00:31:55.246 --> 00:31:57.415
[man] He's still on our ass! Go. go. go!

569
00:31:58.875 --> 00:32:00.293
[boss] Come on!

570
00:32:00.960 --> 00:32:03.463
-[boss panting]
-[man] He's off of us. he's off of us!

571
00:32:03.546 --> 00:32:05.882
-[driver] We did it!
-[man] Holy shit.

572
00:32:05.965 --> 00:32:08.009
[music fades]

573
00:32:08.092 --> 00:32:09.552
[whooshing]

574
00:32:18.102 --> 00:32:20.104
[breathes heavily]

575
00:32:20.188 --> 00:32:21.189
I'm done.

576
00:32:21.898 --> 00:32:23.942
Christ. I am too old!

577
00:32:24.025 --> 00:32:25.026
[men] What?

578
00:32:25.777 --> 00:32:28.488
[boss] I'm retiring
and opening a flour-based food shop.

579
00:32:28.571 --> 00:32:29.781
[man] Flour-based food?

580
00:32:32.158 --> 00:32:34.827
-You know. like Hawaiian pancakes.
-[man] Is he kidding?

581
00:32:35.328 --> 00:32:37.747
Mix a little coconut into your batter.

582
00:32:37.830 --> 00:32:40.208
-You got a Hawaiian pancake.
-[driver] Pancakes?

583
00:32:42.335 --> 00:32:45.129
You know. boss.
my parents run a grocery store.

584
00:32:45.213 --> 00:32:47.882
You can get all the fruit you want there!

585
00:32:47.966 --> 00:32:50.134
-Oh. good idea!
-[laughing]

586
00:32:50.218 --> 00:32:51.803
-You know what?
-What?

587
00:32:52.762 --> 00:32:54.222
Let's put drugs in them.

588
00:32:54.305 --> 00:32:55.640
[man laughs]

589
00:32:55.723 --> 00:32:57.892
-So basically. you're not retiring?
-[laughing]

590
00:33:09.737 --> 00:33:11.572
[low. concerned chatter]

591
00:33:20.039 --> 00:33:21.290
[pedestrian screams]

592
00:33:25.086 --> 00:33:27.422
[Kyoko breathes shakily]

593
00:33:29.173 --> 00:33:31.175
[somber piano music playing]

594
00:34:00.329 --> 00:34:02.040
[music fades out]

595
00:34:02.123 --> 00:34:04.333
[Kenji] Excuse me. Police. Coming though.

596
00:34:04.417 --> 00:34:06.586
-Out of the way!
-[Michiko] Clear a path!

597
00:34:07.837 --> 00:34:10.214
[sirens wailing]

598
00:34:20.475 --> 00:34:21.851
[Kenji exhales]

599
00:34:25.897 --> 00:34:27.899
[mysterious music playing]

600
00:34:42.038 --> 00:34:44.040
[mysterious music continues]

601
00:35:05.520 --> 00:35:10.858
POLICE
METROPOLITAN POLICE DEPARTMENT

602
00:35:13.903 --> 00:35:15.988
[gothic pop music playing on TV]

603
00:35:20.201 --> 00:35:21.869
[man] Ah. that. right there.

604
00:35:22.370 --> 00:35:25.248
That. Hey. That. That.

605
00:35:25.748 --> 00:35:28.042
Look. There.

606
00:35:28.668 --> 00:35:29.544
There.

607
00:35:29.627 --> 00:35:31.629
[intriguing music playing]

608
00:35:37.301 --> 00:35:39.220
It's the Human Vapor.

609
00:35:41.013 --> 00:35:42.390
It's gotta be.

610
00:35:45.685 --> 00:35:48.104
[mysterious music playing]
